TY  - JOUR
T1  - Attributional Influences On The Job Performance–Job Satisfaction Relationship
AU  - Norris, Dwight R.
AU  - Niebuhr, Robert E.
Y1  - 1984/06/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255933
DO  - 10.5465/255933
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 424
EP  - 431
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses research pertaining to the moderating influences of locus of control on the job performance?job satisfaction relationship. Locus of control is a basic personality dimension characterized by the generalized tendency to attribute cause or control of events to internal or external causes. The study was conducted at a medium-sized industrial company employing almost 1,300 workers. Job satisfaction was measured using the Job Description Index. The study indicates that there is a strong relationship between job performance and job satisfaction among those with internal orientations.
AB  - The article discusses research pertaining to the moderating influences of locus of control on the job performance?job satisfaction relationship. Locus of control is a basic personality dimension characterized by the generalized tendency to attribute cause or control of events to internal or external causes. The study was conducted at a medium-sized industrial company employing almost 1,300 workers. Job satisfaction was measured using the Job Description Index. The study indicates that there is a strong relationship between job performance and job satisfaction among those with internal orientations.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255933
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255933
